ions</div><div style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" class="">(and I am sure Ralph will post it shortly, and it might already be in the FAQ)</div><div style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" class=""><br class=""></div><div style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" class="">Cheers,</div><div style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" class=""><br class=""></div><div style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" class="">Gilles</div><div style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" class=""><br class="">On Wednesday, June 22, 2016, Jeff Hammond &lt;<a href="mailto:jeff.science@gmail.com" class="">jeff.science@gmail.com</a>&gt; wrote:<br class=""><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0.8ex; border-left-width: 1px; border-left-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-left-style: solid; padding-left: 1ex;"><font size="2" class=""><span style="background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0);" class="">&nbsp;KMP_AFFINITY is essential for performance. One just needs to set it to something that distributes the threads properly.&nbsp;</span></font><div class=""><font size="2" class=""><span class=""><br class=""></span></font></div><div class=""><font size="2" class=""><span style="background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0);" class=""></span><span class="">Not setting&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0);" class="">KMP_AFFINITY means no affinity and thus inheriting from process affinity mask.</span></font></div><div class=""><font size="2" class=""><span style="background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0);" class=""><br class=""></span></font></div><div class=""><font size="2" class=""><span style="background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0);" class=""></span><span class="">Jeff<br class=""></span></font><br class="">On Wednesday, June 22, 2016, Gilles Gouaillardet &lt;<a target="_blank" class="">gilles@rist.or.jp</a>&gt; wrote:<br class=""><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0.8ex; border-left-width: 1px; border-left-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-left-style: solid; padding-left: 1ex;"><div bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" class=""><p class="">my bad, I was assuming KMP_AFFINITY was used<br class=""></p><p class=""><br class=""></p><p class="">so let me put it this way :</p><p class="">do *not* use KMP_AFFINITY with mpirun -bind-to none, otherwise, you will very likely end up doing time sharing ...</p><p class=""><br class=""></p><p class="">Cheers,</p><p class